 provisional in several senses: shifting across time and space, subject to the availability and movement of resources, and dependent upon shared moral codes and relentless instrumental demands. In the end, she shows that police authority in India is not simply a vulgar manifestation of raw power or the violence of law but, rather, a contingent and volatile social resource relied upon in different ways to help realize human needs and desires in a pluralistic, postcolonial democracy. Provocative and compelling, Provisional Authority provides a rare and disquieting look inside the world of police in India, and shines critical light on an institution fraught with moral, legal and political contradictions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJustice, Administration ofxSocial aspectszIndiazLucknow. 0aJustice, Administration ofxSocial aspectszIndiazUttar Pradesh. 0aPolice corruptionzIndiazLucknow. 0aPolice corruptionzIndiazUttar Pradesh. 0aPolicezIndiazLucknow. 0aPolicezIndiazUttar Pradesh. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aIndia.  aauthority.  acorruption.  acriminalization.  ademocracy.  apolicing.  aprovisionality.  asecurity.  aviolence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022640367040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226403847423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226403847/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles